Na Dravuni e dua na yanuyanu kacabote ena [[Kadavu Yanyanu Ilawalawa]] e Viti. [[Kovuta]] e dua na iwasewase ni 0.8 km2 (0.3 na sq Mi), e tiko ena 18.78° ceva kei 178.53° tokalau, ka yacova yani e dua na na levu cake ena 40 metres (131 ft). 

Na [[Levu Astrolabe Cakau]] e sa dua na itatarovi levu duadua ena vuravura oqo kei na kovuta [[Kadavu]], na yanuyanu o ono kei na yanuyanu lalai tale eso ena loma ni dua na veitaqomaki vakawaitui. Na cakau sa predominantly yani ki na Ceva kei Kadavu e ra kei ark na vualiku kei ono na yanuyanu ena vualiku kei buliya.

Dravuni is also home to The University of the South Pacific (USP) research facility which is currently being used by Coral Cay Conservation (CCC) as the main base for conducting surveys on the reefs by invitation of the Fijian Ministry of Tourism. 
Former Foreign Minister and diplomat Kaliopate Tavola is a native of Dravuni. 

